1
00:00:44,362 --> 00:00:49,137
=The Hidden Heir Ye Chen=
(Adapted from "The Peerless Son-in-Law")

2
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:52,250
=Episode 10=

3
00:00:53,087 --> 00:00:54,486
Please call the witness.

4
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,000
I can testify.

5
00:00:59,039 --> 00:01:00,320
Yunfei!

6
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,280
Why are you here?

7
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,780
Ma'am, here's the evidence.

8
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,640
Xiao Weiwei
and your precious eldest grandson

9
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,920
have been siphoning money
from the Xiao Group

10
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:10,200
straight into their own pockets.

11
00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:11,680
From my accounts alone,

12
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,439
I've funneled them over ten million.

13
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,879
Wang Yunfei, have you lost your mind?!

14
00:01:14,879 --> 00:01:16,300
You just want to dump me, don't you?

15
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:18,439
Trying to cozy up
to Young Master Qin instead?

16
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:19,719
Fine, Xiao Weiwei.

17
00:01:19,959 --> 00:01:21,287
You brought this on yourself.

18
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:46,920
Yunfei, listen to my explanation!

19
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,330
Get lost.

20
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,799
Xiao Weiwei, listen carefully.

21
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:49,599
From today onward,

22
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,480
our engagement

23
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,280
is cancelled!

24
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,680
That's not true!

25
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,799
Yunfei!

26
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,480
Aodong, look!

27
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,400
He's bullying me!

28
00:02:05,599 --> 00:02:06,560
Don't touch me!

29
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:07,799
You're already engaged.

30
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:08,830
Why are you trying to seduce me?

31
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,879
Do you think I'm your backup plan?

32
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,359
Enough!

33
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:13,280
Stop making a scene!

34
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:14,680
Grandma, this isn't a scene.

35
00:02:15,199 --> 00:02:16,520
This concerns the Xiao Group.

36
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:18,680
The Xiao Group

37
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:20,840
was built with Grandpa's blood and sweat,

38
00:02:21,319 --> 00:02:22,919
together with all our relatives here.

39
00:02:23,287 --> 00:02:24,662
This isn't a place where you can

40
00:02:24,662 --> 00:02:25,942
take money whenever you want.

41
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:26,960
Madam,

42
00:02:27,637 --> 00:02:29,520
out of respect for Old Mr. Xiao,

43
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:31,000
we've kept quiet all this time.

44
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,837
But what happened today

45
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,759
has gone too far.

46
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,599
I support Churan.

47
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:38,400
She's young and capable.

48
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:39,159
Same here.

49
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,520
I support Churan too.

50
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:41,800
Grandma,

51
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,319
what do you say?

52
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,680
Should I make

53
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,319
this call to the police... or not?

54
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:49,800
No.

55
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:52,000
I'll follow everyone's opinion.

56
00:02:52,319 --> 00:02:53,360
The position of chairman

57
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,759
should be given to Churan.

58
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:59,888
♪In my heart
I mark the road to rise again♪

59
00:02:59,962 --> 00:03:02,867
♪My future isn't written by fate♪

60
00:03:03,075 --> 00:03:05,280
♪The light is carved open
by my own fists♪

61
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,080
Mr. Qin,

62
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,840
did you enjoy the game?

63
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,680
I told you before.

64
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,840
This has only just begun.

65
00:03:13,119 --> 00:03:15,719
♪Even if the world burns me to ashes♪

66
00:03:15,719 --> 00:03:16,319
Ye Chen,

67
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,400
how dare you set me up?

68
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:19,159
Enough!

69
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,879
Isn't this embarrassing enough?

70
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:22,199
Let's go.

71
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,159
Grandma,

72
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:42,360
we've been kneeling for so long.

73
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,840
That's right, Grandma.

74
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,800
My knees really hurt.

75
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:46,919
Hmph.

76
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:48,479
Useless fools.

77
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,180
An opportunity delivered to your door.
and you still couldn't seize it.

78
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:52,159
Now it hurts, huh?

79
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,950
Where was that attitude earlier?

80
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,080
Grandma,

81
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,287
you're not really going
to give Grandpa's safe key

82
00:04:01,287 --> 00:04:02,488
to Xiao Churan, are you?

83
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,400
Of course not.

84
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,780
You'll take it to her tomorrow.

85
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:08,719
Me?

86
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:12,879
Understood.

87
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,680
Where's your grandpa's medicine jar?

88
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:29,399
Maybe it wasn't put back.

89
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:31,959
Didn't you say
that was the most precious thing

90
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:33,800
your grandpa left behind?

91
00:04:35,279 --> 00:04:36,000
Yeah.

92
00:04:44,879 --> 00:04:45,560
Churan, look.

93
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:51,600
Someone opened the safe today.

94
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:04,199
You're not even good at being a thief.

95
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:06,120
What can you actually do?

96
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,000
Not talking?

97
00:05:10,570 --> 00:05:12,190
If you don't talk,
I'm calling the police.

98
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,319
On what grounds?

99
00:05:14,319 --> 00:05:15,279
That belonged to my grand...

100
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:16,610
You still have the nerve
to mention Grandpa?

101
00:05:17,137 --> 00:05:18,296
How dare you hit me?

102
00:05:18,296 --> 00:05:19,079
You vile woman!

103
00:05:19,079 --> 00:05:20,279
That's for Grandpa!

104
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,399
Still not telling the truth?

105
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:23,439
Wait! Wait!

106
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:25,199
Stop hitting me!

107
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,319
I just wanted to see

108
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:29,000
what Grandpa had left behind,

109
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
so I took the key and opened the safe.

110
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,040
But then I saw

111
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,519
there was nothing valuable inside.

112
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:33,920
I...

113
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,120
I didn't take anything.

114
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:37,279
You still have the nerve to say
you took nothing?

115
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:37,959
I did.

116
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,800
Just a worthless vase.

117
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,639
Worthless vase?

118
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:44,920
That was Grandpa's
most meaningful keepsake!

119
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:45,839
Tell me.

120
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:47,959
Where did you take it?

121
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,560
I...

122
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,800
I sold it.

123
00:05:52,079 --> 00:05:52,990
Who did you sell it to?

124
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,680
A guy called Zhang Ermao

125
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,920
at Tian Street Ghost Market.

126
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:05,279
Good job in beating him!

127
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,500
Anyone who touched Grandpa's things
deserves a beating.

128
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,079
But don't worry.

129
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,959
I'll definitely get it back for you.

130
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,199
But...

131
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:15,000
we're not familiar with Ghost Market.

132
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,600
We might not be

133
00:06:16,839 --> 00:06:17,600
but someone is.

134
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,279
Dad,

135
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,759
why are you eating this?

136
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:28,920
Let me cook a few more dishes for you.

137
00:06:30,199 --> 00:06:30,720
No need.

138
00:06:30,959 --> 00:06:31,900
This is fine.

139
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:34,519
Cream cake with ribbonfish.

140
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,079
I have carbs

141
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,279
and protein.

142
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,990
This is pretty nutritious.

143
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,839
Dad, mom kept asking me about it

144
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:43,759
so I had no choice

145
00:06:43,759 --> 00:06:44,800
but to sell you out.

146
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,000
I knew it was you who told her.

147
00:06:48,519 --> 00:06:49,480
Your mom and I

148
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,240
had a real showdown

149
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,199
over that vase.

150
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,279
Actually, I wanted to ask you,

151
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,078
have you ever been to that Ghost...

152
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:00,759
No.

153
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,398
Then you must know Zhang Er...

154
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,150
Never heard of him.

155
00:07:10,319 --> 00:07:11,000
This is for you.

156
00:07:11,279 --> 00:07:11,959
My apology.

157
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,680
It's from the Ming Dynasty.

158
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,780
Worth several hundred thousand.

159
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,360
This...

160
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:26,380
This is from the Ming Dynasty?

161
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:26,920
Mm.

162
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:28,500
Ming Dynasty Supermarket, you mean?

163
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,240
This is way too fake.

164
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:32,439
This thing

165
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,079
costs several hundred thousand!

166
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,850
Where did you buy it?

167
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:37,399
From Zhang Ermao at Ghost Market.

168
00:07:38,839 --> 00:07:40,040
Oh no...

169
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,519
You've been scammed again.

170
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:43,560
Let me tell you.

171
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,560
That guy's the worst.

172
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:47,040
He used you to scam me.

173
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,519
Eighty percent of the fakes I own

174
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,680
came from him.

175
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,519
We need to find him.

176
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,879
Forget it.

177
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:53,759
The money's already spent.

178
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:55,040
That's several hundred thousand!

179
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:55,439
No!

180
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,580
We're going to find him.

181
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,399
Wait for me.

182
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,199
You're really going?

183
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:01,839
Then hurry up!

184
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,079
Didn't you say
there was no prescription in the safe?

185
00:08:13,079 --> 00:08:14,040
There wasn't!

186
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,720
I already searched through everything.

187
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:16,800
How would I know

188
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,000
that the vase you mentioned

189
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:19,759
had anything to do
with some prescription?

190
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:20,199
You!

191
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:20,959
Dad,

192
00:08:21,399 --> 00:08:22,160
don't be angry.

193
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:23,900
I'll go get it back for you right now.

194
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:24,639
Hmm.

195
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,000
Get lost!

196
00:08:32,687 --> 00:08:33,387
(Under the old tree at sunset)

197
00:08:33,412 --> 00:08:34,525
(Spring sails on the river)

198
00:08:34,550 --> 00:08:36,025
(Tian Street Ghost Market)

199
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,550
(Blow your own sugar figurines.
Please enter)

200
00:08:45,050 --> 00:08:46,762
(Zhang Ermao Antiques)

201
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:52,279
What are you knocking for?

202
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,320
Zhang Ermao!

203
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,679
Mr. Xiao.

204
00:08:58,279 --> 00:08:59,159
What brings you here?

205
00:08:59,159 --> 00:09:00,080
Cut the fake smiles.

206
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,360
This thing cost several hundred thousand?

207
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:03,440
Have you no shame?

208
00:09:03,799 --> 00:09:04,200
He

209
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,600
is my son-in-law.

210
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:07,399
Your son-in-law?

211
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,279
No, wait.

212
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:09,120
Mr. Xiao,

213
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,120
don't be mad.

214
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,399
Listen, this item is worth it.

215
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:13,080
It...

216
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:17,159
Wait... I mean.

217
00:09:17,159 --> 00:09:18,850
This wasn't even sold by me!

218
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:19,287
No!

219
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,039
I don't even know

220
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,320
your son-in-law.

221
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,480
So now you're denying it?

222
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,080
Let me tell you.

223
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,279
You better return the money today,

224
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,600
or I'll report you
to the police station.

225
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,990
- You'll end up in prison!
- Dad! Dad!

226
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,279
I got the wrong person.

227
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:29,660
He's not the one who sold it to me.

228
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,960
We were about to start a fight
and you're messing with me?

229
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,279
Alright, calm down.

230
00:09:34,279 --> 00:09:35,799
What's the point of him calming down?

231
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:37,080
I'm still furious!

232
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:40,000
You bring this junk here,
claim it's expensive, and frame me?

233
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Alright, fine.

234
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:43,159
Since we're already here,
how about this?

235
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:44,799
Show us what good stuff you've got.

236
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:45,560
Bring them all out.

237
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,639
Dude, you're good.

238
00:09:48,639 --> 00:09:49,759
Wait a minute.

239
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:51,279
Weren't we here to defend our rights?

240
00:09:51,279 --> 00:09:52,159
Now we're shopping?

241
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,759
Just one look.

242
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,600
Mr. Xiao,

243
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,320
money's meant to be spent, right?

244
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,360
Why not spend it here?

245
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:57,879
Look.

246
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,799
(Baishi)
Take a look.

247
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:01,879
Emperor Huizong of Song's

248
00:10:01,879 --> 00:10:02,919
Slender Gold calligraphy.

249
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:04,240
How is it?

250
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,080
You should lose some weight.

251
00:10:06,350 --> 00:10:07,519
What's that got to do with me?

252
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:08,480
I call this being carefree...

253
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,480
I meant the writing.

254
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,720
Doesn't it say Qi Baishi right there?

255
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,275
(Baishi)

256
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,399
Wrong piece.

257
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,480
Look at this one.

258
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:17,800
An imperial kiln piece
from the Yongle reign

259
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:18,600
of the Ming Dynasty.

260
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:20,399
Why not just say it's
from Qin Shi Huang?

261
00:10:21,879 --> 00:10:23,150
Lotus scroll with window panels.

262
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:25,675
If this were genuine,
it should be from the Qianlong era.

263
00:10:26,362 --> 00:10:27,840
Why does it have a fake shine?

264
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,320
What fake shine?

265
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:31,162
That's what you call
"old but well preserved".

266
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,240
Texture.

267
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,519
Texture is what matters.

268
00:10:33,862 --> 00:10:36,480
Ming porcelain usually has sand stuck
on the base rim.

269
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,590
It feels rough to the touch.

270
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:41,240
Doesn't it say Qianlong right there?

271
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,062
(Made during the Qianlong reign)

272
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,562
My mistake. It's Qianlong's.

273
00:10:46,862 --> 00:10:48,062
I ought to have you arrested.

274
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,000
Mr. Xiao,

275
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,799
with such a capable son-in-law,

276
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:52,600
why bother buying fakes?

277
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,399
Are you addicted to it?

278
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,320
I just met him as well.

279
00:10:58,159 --> 00:10:59,990
If you don't have anything good,
we're leaving.

280
00:11:01,399 --> 00:11:02,480
If word gets out

281
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:04,679
that Zhang Ermao has no good stuff,
that'd be a joke.

282
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:05,919
Wait.

283
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,279
Take a look.

284
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,120
This belongs to my dad.

285
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,000
Don't flatter me.

286
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,960
I have a son already.

287
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,440
Tch!

288
00:11:21,679 --> 00:11:22,720
Who's talking to you?

289
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,919
Chen, this belonged to my dad,

290
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:26,120
your grandpa-in-law.

291
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,320
Then we've got to get it back.

292
00:11:27,799 --> 00:11:28,720
Well...

293
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,175
this piece looks ordinary.

294
00:11:31,175 --> 00:11:32,490
I believe it's about 20 yuan only.

295
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,299
Alright.

296
00:11:33,399 --> 00:11:34,440
I'll offer you 30 yuan.

297
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,080
I'll take it.

298
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,159
Thirty?

299
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,200
This item is mine.

300
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,960
This shop is mine.

301
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,200
And I set the price.

302
00:11:45,879 --> 00:11:47,600
I take no less than 100...

303
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:50,514
One million!

304
00:11:50,639 --> 00:11:51,799
I take one million!

305
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,440
What?

306
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,679
Have you no shame?

307
00:11:54,799 --> 00:11:56,519
This was originally ours!

308
00:11:56,519 --> 00:11:58,360
Let's be honest here.

309
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,399
Kid,

310
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:00,759
you came here

311
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:02,879
for this, didn't you?

312
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:05,759
Bro,

313
00:12:05,759 --> 00:12:06,399
let's talk.

314
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,240
Sure. Let's talk.

315
00:12:09,637 --> 00:12:10,875
(Zhang Ermao Antiques)

316
00:12:34,375 --> 00:12:36,863
♪They said I was only meant
to gaze at the light♪

317
00:12:36,950 --> 00:12:40,703
♪Never knowing I am the flame itself♪

318
00:12:41,163 --> 00:12:46,100
♪I am fireworks, not a fire cast aside♪

319
00:12:46,263 --> 00:12:48,550
♪I open my eyes amid the ruins♪

320
00:12:48,863 --> 00:12:51,543
♪No one shields me
from the wind or the sky♪

321
00:12:52,613 --> 00:12:55,238
♪Let them mock, let them sneer♪

322
00:12:55,538 --> 00:12:58,550
♪I sharpen my silence into blades♪

323
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:01,800
♪Every cold word, I remember♪

324
00:13:01,913 --> 00:13:04,875
♪Etching my path of defiance
into my heart♪

325
00:13:05,143 --> 00:13:08,300
♪Fate did not sign my future for me♪

326
00:13:08,525 --> 00:13:12,275
♪I carved my own light
with clenched fists♪

327
00:13:12,275 --> 00:13:15,138
♪I belong to no one♪

328
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:18,650
♪I am the ember
that refuses to bow to destiny♪

329
00:13:18,650 --> 00:13:21,325
♪Even if the world burns me into ash♪

330
00:13:21,325 --> 00:13:27,663
♪I will rise upon those ashes♪
